article.description: — Jahmir Young scored 21 points including a 3-pointer for Charlotte's final basket and an eight-point lead with a minute to go and the 49ers beat Southern Miss 70-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Young helps Charlotte beat Southern Miss 70-67
article.linkText: Young helps Charlotte beat Southern Miss 70-67
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. -- — Jahmir Young scored 21 points including a 3-pointer for Charlotte's final basket and an eight-point lead with a minute to go and the 49ers beat Southern Miss 70-67 on Saturday. Austin Butler had 16 points for Charlotte (17-13, 10-8 Conference USA). Jackson Threadgill added 10 points. Isaih Moore had 20 points and 13 rebounds for the Golden Eagles (6-25, 1-17), who have now lost 14 consecutive games. DeAndre Pinckney added 17 points. Walyn Napper had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
